subject: Soccer
lead_paragraph: Arsenal lost its first game of the English Premier League season, falling at Middlesbrough, 2-1. Arsenal still has a one-point lead in the standings.Stewart Downing and Tuncay Sanli scored to give Middlesbrough its first win in any competition since Sept. 1. Tomas Rosicky scored in injury time for Arsenal.Arsenal leads the league with 37 points, followed by Manchester United with 36 and Chelsea with 34.
